I"ç<p>When presented with a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/qualia-provide-experiential-knowledge">monochromatic</a> enveloping wall for <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/time-is-a-relevant-dimension-of-attention">multiple minutes in a row</a>, subjects report gradually losing the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/conscious-unconscious-divide-has-edge-cases">conscious experience</a> of color. In this, Ganzfeld stimulation results in a collapse of conscious experience, especially so in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/sensory-deprivation-supports-neuroimaging-of-mental-imagery">sensory deprivation</a>.</p>
